    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/DdHww.jpg?s=256",
            "account_id": 4237775,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 3468485,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3468485/omar",
            "reputation": 301,
            "display_name": "omar"
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 1,
        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1441087914,
        "creation_date": 1441087914,
        "body": "<p>You can do this by creating a custom view and set it to the action bar<\/p>\n\n<p>myTextView layout file:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;RelativeLayout xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\nandroid:layout_width=\"match_parent\" android:layout_height=\"match_parent\"&gt;\n\n&lt;TextView\n    android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:singleLine=\"true\"\n    android:layout_centerInParent=\"true\"\n    android:text=\"This is a very looooooooooooong text.\"/&gt;\n\n&lt;/RelativeLayout&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And in onCreate method you just set it to the action bar:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>getActionBar().setCustomView(R.layout.myTextView);\ngetActionBar().setDisplayShowCustomEnabled(true);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Im not sure if there is a more straightforward way, but this should work. <\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 32324691,
        "question_id": 32246783
    }],
